notes: The LLM output states 'safe' with 0.85 confidence and reports 0 findings. It completely missed the target vulnerability in getSwapFee where governance-configured fees above 100_000 ppm (10%) are silently discarded and fall back to the tick-spacing default. The ground truth describes a logic error where the module allows fees up to 50% but the factory clamps to 10% without notification, causing governance to believe higher fees are active when they are not. Since no findings were reported, the target was not found.
